text: Johanna Maria "Annie" Jelles (born 1941) is a Dutch road cyclist from Amsterdam. She competed at the 1959 UCI Road World Championships, in the women's road race event. That was the first time, that the Dutch governing body KNWU sent female athletes to the World Championships*. As of 2020, she is still cycling and lives in Scharwoude. == References == Category:1941 births Category:Dutch cyclists Category:Living people
